article.headline: SMS 110, Troy 63
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo.(AP) -- Anthony Shavies scored 22 points to lead Southwest Missouri State over Troy 110-63 Saturday night. Southwest Missouri (5-1) had little trouble with Troy (1-6) in a game that was decided in the first half. Troy shot just 30 percent from the field and made only two field goals in the first 12:30. Southwest Missouri shot 62 percent from the field and led 52-28 at halftime. The Bears opened the second half with a 28-10 run to lead 80-38 with 12:55 left. Southwest Missouri outscored Troy 42-18 in the paint. The last time Southwest Missouri scored 100 points was in 1996 against Troy, winning 105-81. Blake Ahearn scored 20 points, including five 3-pointers, for Southwest Missouri. Deke Thompson and Tamarr Maclin scored 12 points each, Kellen Easlin had 11 and Drew Richards added 10. Ryan Heck led Troy with 12 points.
